   "source": [
    "## Identify the Dependent Variable\n",
    "\n",
    "The dependent variable can be `label` if the goal is binary classification: predicting whether a network connection is normal or attack traffic. The dependent variable can also be `type` if the goal is multiclass classification: predicting the specific attack category. For our first model, `label` is the simpler dependent variable because it only has two classes: 0 for normal and 1 for attack."
   ]
  },
